@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Study Materials Help";
}

<div class="container mt-4">
    <nav aria-label="breadcrumb">
        <ol class="breadcrumb">
            <li class="breadcrumb-item"><a asp-controller="Help" asp-action="Index">Help</a></li>
            <li class="breadcrumb-item active" aria-current="page">Study Materials</li>
        </ol>
    </nav>

    <div class="d-flex align-items-center mb-4">
        <div class="me-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="48" height="48" fill="currentColor" class="bi bi-folder-open text-primary" viewBox="0 0 16 16">
                <path d="M1 3.5A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 2.5 2h2.764c.958 0 1.76.56 2.311 1.184C7.985 3.648 8.48 4 9 4h4.5A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 15 5.5v.64c.57.265.94.876.856 1.546l-.64 5.124A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 12.733 15H3.266a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-2.481-2.19l-.64-5.124A1.5 1.5 0 0 1 1 6.14V3.5zM2 6h12v-.5a.5.5 0 0 0-.5-.5H9c-.964 0-1.71-.629-2.174-1.154C6.374 3.334 5.82 3 5.264 3H2.5a.5.5 0 0 0-.5.5V6zm-.367 1a.5.5 0 0 0-.496.562l.64 5.124A1.5 1.5 0 0 0 3.266 14h9.468a1.5 1.5 0 0 0 1.489-1.314l.64-5.124A.5.5 0 0 0 14.367 7H1.633z"/>
            </svg>
        </div>
        <div>
            <h1 class="mb-0">Study Materials Help</h1>
            <p class="text-muted mb-0">Learn how to upload and manage your custom study content</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <section id="overview" class="mb-5">
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>
            Study Materials allow you to customize StudyHelper with your own content. Upload markdown files containing 
            questions, terms, or equations to personalize quizzes, flashcards, and exercises to match your curriculum 
            or study needs.
        </p>
        <div class="alert alert-info">
            <strong>Note:</strong> If you don't upload custom materials, StudyHelper uses default content for all study features.
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="getting-started" class="mb-5">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
                <h3 class="mb-0">Getting Started</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Navigate:</strong> Go to Settings → Study Materials</li>
                    <li><strong>Choose Material Type:</strong> Select Questions, Terms, or Equations</li>
                    <li><strong>Upload File:</strong> Click "Choose File" and select your markdown (.md) file</li>
                    <li><strong>Submit:</strong> Click "Upload" to save your custom content</li>
                    <li><strong>Verify:</strong> Your study features will now use your uploaded content</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="study-preferences" class="mb-5">
        <div class="card border-info">
            <div class="card-header bg-info text-white">
                <h3 class="mb-0">
                    <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" fill="currentColor" class="bi bi-sliders me-2" viewBox="0 0 16 16">
                        <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M11.5 2a1.5 1.5 0 1 0 0 3 1.5 1.5 0 0 0 0-3zM9.05 3a2.5 2.5 0 0 1 4.9 0H16v1h-2.05a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-4.9 0H0V3h9.05zM4.5 7a1.5 1.5 0 1 0 0 3 1.5 1.5 0 0 0 0-3zM2.05 8a2.5 2.5 0 0 1 4.9 0H16v1H6.95a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-4.9 0H0V8h2.05zm9.45 4a1.5 1.5 0 1 0 0 3 1.5 1.5 0 0 0 0-3zm-2.45 1a2.5 2.5 0 0 1 4.9 0H16v1h-2.05a2.5 2.5 0 0 1-4.9 0H0v-1h9.05z"/>
                    </svg>
                    Study Preferences
                </h3>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5>Enable/Disable Equation-Based Features</h5>
                <p>
                    You can control which study features appear on your home page. If you're focusing on terms and definitions 
                    and don't need equation practice, you can disable equation-based features:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Exercise:</strong> Accounting equation problem solving</li>
                    <li><strong>Graded Exercises:</strong> Scored equation assessments</li>
                    <li><strong>Equation Flashcards:</strong> Formula review and practice</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="mt-3"><strong>How to toggle equation features:</strong></p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Navigate to Settings → Study Materials</li>
                    <li>Scroll to the "Study Preferences" section</li>
                    <li>Use the toggle switch to enable or disable "Equation-Based Features"</li>
                    <li>Click "Save Preferences" to apply your changes</li>
                </ol>
                <div class="alert alert-info mt-3">
                    <strong>Note:</strong> Disabling equation features hides them from the home page, but your uploaded 
                    equation files remain saved. You can re-enable these features anytime. Quiz, Graded Quiz, and Term 
                    Flashcards remain visible regardless of this setting.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="file-formats" class="mb-5">
        <h2>File Formats</h2>
        <p>All study materials must be in markdown (.md) format with specific structures:</p>

        <h4>Questions File</h4>
        <p>Used by Quiz and Graded Quiz features.</p>
        <pre class="bg-light p-3"><code>## Question 1
What is the accounting equation?

- Assets = Liabilities + Equity (correct)
- Revenue - Expenses = Net Income
- Assets + Liabilities = Equity
- Revenue + Expenses = Profit

Explanation: The fundamental accounting equation shows that assets are financed by liabilities and equity.</code></pre>

        <h4>Terms File</h4>
        <p>Used by Term Flashcards.</p>
        <pre class="bg-light p-3"><code>## Asset
A resource owned by a business that provides future economic benefits.

## Liability
An obligation or debt that a business owes to external parties.</code></pre>

        <h4>Equations File</h4>
        <p>Used by Exercise, Graded Exercises, and Equation Flashcards.</p>
        <pre class="bg-light p-3"><code">## Net Income
Net Income = Revenue - Expenses

Variables:
- Net Income: Profit or loss for a period
- Revenue: Total income earned
- Expenses: Total costs incurred</code></pre>
    </section>

    <section id="tips" class="mb-5">
        <h2>Tips & Best Practices</h2>
        <div class="alert alert-success">
            <strong>Start Small:</strong> Upload a file with 10-20 items first to test formatting before adding more content.
        </div>
        <div class="alert alert-success">
            <strong>Check Formatting:</strong> Ensure your markdown follows the exact structure shown above—spacing and headings matter.
        </div>
        <div class="alert alert-success">
            <strong>Mark Correct Answers:</strong> For questions, always add "(correct)" after the right answer choice.
        </div>
        <div class="alert alert-warning">
            <strong>Important:</strong> Files must be UTF-8 encoded markdown (.md) files. Other formats will be rejected.
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="related" class="mb-5">
        <div class="card bg-light">
            <div class="card-header"><h3 class="mb-0">Related Topics</h3></div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                        <h5>Quiz</h5>
                        <p>Learn how custom questions are used in the Quiz feature.</p>
                        <a asp-controller="Help" asp-action="Quiz" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-primary">Learn More →</a>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-6 mb-3">
                        <h5>Exercise</h5>
                        <p>Understand how custom equations power the Exercise feature.</p>
                        <a asp-controller="Help" asp-action="Exercise" class="btn btn-sm btn-outline-primary">Learn More →</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <div class="text-center mb-4">
        <a asp-controller="Help" asp-action="Index" class="btn btn-outline-secondary">← Back to Help Overview</a>
    </div>
</div>
